### Phase 5 — Backlog slice smoke tests (UC-4, UC-6, UC-7, UC-7.1, UC-7.2, BR-2)
### Prereqs: backend on http://localhost:8080 with seeded users (pm/ba/emp).
### Usage (IntelliJ HTTP client or VSCode REST Client): run requests top-to-bottom;
### variables {{pmToken}}, {{baToken}}, {{goalId}}, {{backlogId}}, {{itemId}} are
### captured via the response handlers below.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### 1. PM login
# @name pmLogin
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username": "pm", "password": "pmPass1!"}

> {% client.global.set("pmToken", response.body.token); %}

### 2. BA login
# @name baLogin
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username": "ba", "password": "baPass1!"}

> {% client.global.set("baToken", response.body.token); %}

### 3. EMPLOYEE login
# @name empLogin
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username": "emp", "password": "empPass1!"}

> {% client.global.set("empToken", response.body.token); %}

### 4. PM creates a goal (backlog needs a parent goal; BR-2) → 201
# @name createGoal
POST {{host}}/api/v1/goals
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Цель под бэклог Q1",
  "periodStart": "2026-01-01",
  "periodEnd": "2026-12-31",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "kpis": [{"name": "KPI-1", "targetValue": 100, "currentValue": 0, "unit": "шт."}]
}

> {% client.global.set("goalId", response.body.id); %}

### 5. BA creates a DRAFT backlog with 2 items (UC-4, UC-6) → 201
# @name createBacklog
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Бэклог Q1",
  "goalId": "{{goalId}}",
  "items": [
    {"title": "Интеграция платёжного шлюза", "description": "Stripe + 3DS", "priority": "HIGH"},
    {"title": "Модуль отчётности", "description": "Excel-экспорт", "priority": "MEDIUM"}
  ]
}

> {% client.global.set("backlogId", response.body.id);
     client.global.set("itemId", response.body.items[0].id); %}

### 6. BA adds one more item to the DRAFT (UC-6) → 200
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/items
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"title": "Личный кабинет клиента", "description": "SSO + профиль", "priority": "LOW"}

### 7. BA updates an item (UC-6) → 200
PATCH {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/items/{{itemId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"title": "Интеграция Stripe", "description": "Stripe + 3DS + webhooks", "priority": "CRITICAL"}

### 8. BA submits for approval (DRAFT → SUBMITTED, UC-7) → 200
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}

### 9. BA tries to sign their own backlog → 403 (UC-7.1 reserved for PM)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/sign
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}

### 10. BA tries to edit items after submit → 400 (item mutation locked)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/items
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"title": "Поздняя правка", "priority": "LOW"}

### 11. PM lists backlogs (sees all) → 200
GET {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 12. BA lists backlogs (only own) → 200, createdBy = "ba"
GET {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}

### 13. EMPLOYEE tries to list backlogs → 403
GET {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs
Authorization: Bearer {{empToken}}

### 14. PM reads the full backlog → 200
GET {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 15. PM signs the submitted backlog (SUBMITTED → SIGNED, UC-7.1) → 200
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/sign
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 16. PM re-sign attempt → 400 (SIGNED is terminal)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/sign
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 17. PM cancel attempt on SIGNED backlog → 400
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}

### 18. BA creates a second backlog to test cancel flow (UC-7.2) → 201
# @name createBacklog2
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Бэклог под отмену",
  "goalId": "{{goalId}}",
  "items": [{"title": "Временная задача", "priority": "LOW"}]
}

> {% client.global.set("backlogId2", response.body.id); %}

### 19. BA submits the second backlog → 200
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId2}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{baToken}}

### 20. PM cancels the submitted backlog (SUBMITTED → CANCELLED, UC-7.2) → 200
POST {{host}}/api/v1/backlogs/{{backlogId2}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{pmToken}}
